  "?\tBuilding access - ECS will not be available for general access until Monday morning at 5": "00 AM.  Due to the gas and power moves being combined, it is unlikely that the move team will be prepared for the POC's to come in on Sunday to unpack.  (Separate instructions will be generated for those who are needed to test trading applications.)  NOTE: Only those whose names have been approved and submitted to security will be allowed access on Sunday.",
  "?\tLaptops - Important - Please ensure that all cable locks have been removed from all laptop computers by 5": "00 PM on Friday.  If any cable locks are left on the computers they will be destroyed by the move team in order to move the computers as scheduled.",
  "?\tVoicemail instructions - Please have everyone in your group clear all new voicemail messages by 5": "00 PM, Friday, 11/16.  All saved messages, greetings and recorded names will be saved.  If a message is left before cutover the message will be saved, but the message light will not be displayed when you arrive.  As a precautionary meassure please check voice mail upon your arrival Monday morning even if the message light isn't on.",

  "Core": "Wholesale energy business in North America and Europe, retail energy, pipelines",
  "Date": "Wed, 14 Nov 2001 09:44:01 -0800 (PST)",
  "Enron's business has been grouped into three buckets": "Core, Non-core, and Under Review.",
  "From": "patrick.tucker@enron.com",
  "McMahon": "\"The company is overlevered; that's a fact.\"--hence our pursuit of additional equity.",
  "McMahon described the major off-balance-sheet vehicles": "",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c5238065.1075861167355.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Non-core": "Broadband, water, and international assets (i.e. EGAS).  Enron has approx. $8Bn in investments in these assets, and they have produced 'dismal' returns.  Enron will be exiting these businesses and will attempt to wind them up in an orderly fashion.  An aggressive divestiture program has been set in motion for these assets.",
  "Subject": "Highlights from ENE Analyst Conference Call 11/14",
  "To": "s..pollan@enron.com, lindsay.culotta@enron.com, e.murrell@enron.com,",
  "Under Review": "EGM, EIM.  These businesses are being closely examined to determine whether they have a reasonable chance of long-term viability.   "LONGER TERM": "We are projecting NASDAQ 100 to 2450 and the S \u0026 P futures to 1400. This should take until Dec. 2002 to completely manifest, with a secondary high into March 2003. There could be a rocky period into May 2002 but then strong upside into Sept. 2002 and continuing higher into Dec. 2002.",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c26267077.1075840983951.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Or call order": "1-800-788-2796",
  "STOCKS AND MARCH S \u0026 P": "(01/18) Stocks still have not rallied enough to confirm that the current downside correction is over. We may have to wait until Jan. 22-23 for a bottom to finish, and it still could be all the way at 1121 on S \u0026 P futures or max. 1112. We expect that once this correction is over, the market should recover into Feb. 8 or so. If the rally is not impulsive enough and remains corrective, we will remain open to a low into Feb. 22. Worst downside is a move back to 9481 on DOW cash, with support at 9642 on DOW cash and 1530 on NASDAQ 100 cash.",

Reader comments and ideas are always welcomed at: \u003ca href=\"mailto:feedback@skimoguls.com\"\u003efeedback@skimoguls.com\u003c/a\u003e",

  "Subject": "Kids Fly Free to Whistler / Banff!",
  "Telluride - Some say it was named for Tellurium, a gold-bearing ore. Others call it \"To Hell You Ride,\" emphasizing the boisterousness of the 1880's mining town. Surrounded by the largest concentration of 14,000-foot mountains in North America, there's nothing quite like the small town of Telluride. This translates into virtually nonexistent lift lines, and slopes all to yourself": "steep ones, easy ones, long ones -- a mountain for the whole family. This Telluride prize package includes a 5 night stay with ResortQuest and 2 adult four-day lifts",
  "This week Moguls' Mountain Travel Review visits Telluride, Colorado. One of my favorite resorts in Colorado, Telluride captures the essence of a great ski town": "inspiring scenery; great skiing and riding; cozy and convenient lodging and great food and drink. The town of Telluride is tucked neatly into a dramatic box canyon, walled in by the huge, stunning peaks of the San Juan mountain range. Telluride ski resort climbs out of this canyon to a ridge high above the town. From there, ski trails radiate in all directions. The skiing is incredible, with a variety of slopes for all abilities. When the slopes close, this little mountain town comes alive. The quality and variety of restaurants is immediately apparent and an apr?s ski party is easy to find!",
  "To": "mountain-travel@lists.skimoguls.com",

  "To have an agent contact you, visit our website and fill out a \u003ca href=\"http": "//www.moguls.com/packages/index.cfm?DPID=11\u0026lim=q\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color : orange; text-decoration : underline;\"\u003etrip quote\u003c/a\u003e request form. You may also explore our numerous mountain vacation \u003ca href=\"http://www.moguls.com/packages/index.cfm?DPID=11\u0026lim=p\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color : orange; text-decoration : underline;\"\u003epackages\u003c/a\u003e on-line. If you prefer the direct route, give us a call to speak directly with a reservations specialist.\u003cp /\u003e",

  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Subject": "KOMP Horticultural - Sale of Leased Plants",
  "The KOMP Horticultural contract for the maintenance of leased floor plants has been cancelled.  Plant maintenance is not being performed on the leased plants in the Enron Building on floors 3 through 49.  Rather than removing the plants from the building, KOMP Horticultural has chosen to offer the plants to Enron employees for sale.  On January 16th from 11": "00 AM to 2:00 PM, KOMP will have a table on the south side of the plaza, by the up escalator, for those employees interested in purchasing a plant. At the time of purchase, KOMP will give a special sticker to place on the container of the sold plant (do not bring plants to the plaza for purchase).  Plants will not be allowed to be removed from the building unless they have the KOMP sold sticker on the container.",

  "Check out Pine Ridge at \u003ca href='http": "//moguls.com/ski/nl_PineRidge' target='_blank' style='color : #ffffcc; text-decoration : underline; font-weight : bold'\u003ehttp://moguls.com/ski/nl_PineRidge\u003c/a\u003e",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Wed, 9 Jan 2002 20:50:50 -0800 (PST)",
  "From": "mtr@skimoguls.com",
  "Have a group of 20 or more? Direct inquiries to": "\u003ca href=\"mailto:groups@skimoguls.com\" style=\"color : orange; text-decoration : underline;\"\u003egroups@skimoguls.com\u003c/a\u003e",
  "If you are having problems or have questions about this newsletter, please contact us at": "\u003ca href=\"mailto:sales@skimoguls.com\"\u003esales@skimoguls.com\u003c/a\u003e. Reader comments and ideas are always welcomed at: \u003ca href=\"mailto:feedback@skimoguls.com\"\u003efeedback@skimoguls.com\u003c/a\u003e",
  "If your email program does not read HTML, please sign up for our plain-text newsletter by sending a blank email to the following address": "join-mountain-travel-text@lists.skimoguls.com",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c7650677.1075840992859.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Subject": "Happy 2002 skiers and riders!",
  "The Banff Springs Hotel, the Chateau Lake Louise and Banff's three ski resorts have offered and exclusive deal to Moguls and our clients who use their MasterCard to pay for their ski vacation. Stay in a deluxe room at either hotel for the price of a regular room. MasterCard users also receive 3 free breakfasts during their stay, one at each of Banff's 3 resorts. Prices start at $389 per person and packages are based on 2 people traveling. For more details, click here": "",
  "This Olympic year is off to a great start with excellent ski conditions coast to coast (if only Buffalo, N.Y. was a ski resort!). We have a few New Year's resolutions here at Moguls": "To give our clients the very best ski and snowboard vacations we can; To get people traveling and prove that the free people of the world will not be deterred and get out on the slopes ourselves as much as possible! To that end, we have several awesome offers for you. Read on for more details!",
  "To": "mountain-travel@lists.skimoguls.com",
  "To have an agent contact you, visit our website and fill out a \u003ca href=\"http": "//www.moguls.com/packages/index.cfm?DPID=11\u0026lim=q\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color : orange; text-decoration : underline;\"\u003etrip quote\u003c/a\u003e request form. You may also explore our numerous mountain vacation \u003ca href=\"http://www.moguls.com/packages/index.cfm?DPID=11\u0026lim=p\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color : orange; text-decoration : underline;\"\u003epackages\u003c/a\u003e on-line. If you prefer the direct route, give us a call to speak directly with a reservations specialist.\u003cp /\u003e",
  "To unsubscribe send a blank email to": "\u003ca href=\"mailto:leave-mountain-travel-9164A@lists.skimoguls.com\"\u003eleave-mountain-travel-9164A@lists.skimoguls.com\u003c/a\u003e",
  "To view all of our exclusive MasterCard deals, just click here": "\u003ca href='http://moguls.com/ski/MasterCardSpecial' target='_blank' style='color : #ffffcc; text-decoration : underline; font-weight : bold'\u003ehttp://moguls.com/ski/MasterCardSpecial\u003c/a\u003e",
  "Visit GearDrect here": "",
  "We hope you enjoy these mountain travel updates. You are currently subscribed to the Mountain Travel Review as": "alewis@ect.enron.com",

  "Message-ID": "\u003c27873682.1075840994687.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Subject": "Organizational Announcement",
  "The Creditors' Committee was formed last week by the United States Trustee.  This committee is comprised of 15 individuals representing various creditor groups including": "banks, bondholders, insurance companies and employees.  The Creditors' Committee will be the key point of contact as we reorganize the company and emerge from Chapter 11.  Initially, they will send financial advisors to our offices to monitor any asset liquidations as well as review our cash flow projections.  Ultimately, they will be responsible for approving our reorganization plan as to which assets or businesses we sell and which ones we retain.",
  "To": "dl-ga-all_enron_worldwide1@enron.com",
  "Unfortunately, due to the current financial condition of the company, the following members of the management committee have left the company or will be leaving the company by the end of December": "",

  "You have been selected by Lavorato to review and validate gas curves for your region from 12/01/01 forward.   "June 8, 2001 - Yesterday's lack of an earnings warning from Intel (NASDAQ": "JNPR) was good news, but this morning's warning from Juniper Networks (NASDAQ:JNPR) was anything but.",
  "Linux/Open Source            http": "//internet.com/linux",
  "Looking for a job? Filling an opening? - http": "//jobs.internet.com",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c24307290.1075845229441.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Oddly, this is probably worse news for Ciena (NASDAQ": "CIEN), which is now the only telecom equipment company whose earnings are still holding up, than it is for Cisco (NASDAQ:CSCO), Juniper's chief competitor in the router business. Cisco focuses more on the enterprise market, while Ciena has substantial carrier exposure. It will be interesting to see if demand for Ciena's optical equipment can withstand a shakeout in the carrier business, which the Juniper warning signals is clearly underway.   "**The market continued to trade within a narrow range,  which is typical on he days when the contracts \"roll\" .  Front month  in the S\u0026P 500, DJ 100, Nasdaq 100. etc.  is NOW the September contract  (Symbol \"U\").  Days like today can be tough trading days especially if  there is not significant buying or selling in the market.  The MAY Chain  Store sales came out at 9": "00 CST today and I acyually expected the market to  rally off of the number, but many of the retailers reported less than expected  sales.
